  "text": "In the present study, we attempted to couple statedependent behaviour in cod larvae and early juveniles with the 2 most important vertical cues in the environment: temperature and light. In this context, larval state is defined as physiological condition determined by stomach fullness. A system of experimental vertical columns developed earlier [CITATION_1] ) was used to test whether larval cod alter their response to temperature gradients according to food deprivation. In addition, to assess whether a potential state-dependent vertical behaviour was affected by light level and gradients, the light was periodically projected from above and below. Depthstratified sampling of individuals at the end of each trial also enabled us to test whether the vertical distribution was independent of relative size at a given age or stage.",
